news.title: Guideline value hiked to bridge gap with market value: Tamil Nadu minister
news.para: Moorthy said the guideline values were far below the market values in major cities like Chennai, Coimbatore and Madurai, owing to which government and private sector employees found it difficult to raise bank loans to buy properties.

news.title: Housing plot sales surge in Rajasthan; double stamp duty hits flats
news.para: While the natural preference to own one’s roof is a compelling reason, the stamp duty structure has also been major reason behind the spike. But developers feel rampant plotting could contribute to chaotic growth of city.

news.title: Haryana CM tells officials to create separate dashboard for all properties of HSVP
news.para: The chief minister, who is also the chairman of HSPV, was presiding over the 125th meeting of the authority here, according to an official statement.

news.title: Residents protest in Dehradun over delayed probe in Orchid Park case
news.para: The residents said they had lodged an FIR over three years ago and only a few months back, a charge sheet was filed in the matter.

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram corporation sets record in property tax collection, grosses Rs 115 crore
news.para: An updated database of tax dues and aggressive endorsement of online payment of property tax has created a record of sorts in collection with the corporation grossing Rs 115 crore as property tax in 2022-23, as per the latest figures presented in the budget document for 2023-24.

news.title: Jaipur development body demolishes four illegal colonies in Sanganer
news.para: The first colony that was demolished was coming up on land of about 3 bighas in Bhater village. The second colony was in the name of Laxmi Nagar at the same village on land measuring approximately 10 bighas.

news.title: Delhi: 23,000 new flats to be on offer in DDA's upcoming scheme
news.para: During the launch, DDA plans to put on hold sale of around 16,000 flats under the old schemes for one or two months to avoid confusion.

news.title: New York's Flatiron Building fetches $190 million at auction
news.para: The 22-story skyscraper, built in 1902 and often said to resemble a clothes iron, fetched almost four times the opening price of $50 million following a keen bidding war.

news.title: Mortgagee entitled to relief on property acquisition: Karnataka HC
news.para: Allowing the petition filed by DBS Bank, Justice Krishna S Dixit has directed the special land acquisition officer (SLAO), Tumakuru- Chitradurga-Davanagere New Direct Railway Line Project, to refer the petitioner's claim forthwith to 1st Additional District Court, Chitradurga, with all necessary papers.

news.title: Sports City: Noida authority sends notice to Three-C Green Developers
news.para: Three-C Green Developers was allotted 180 acres in the three sectors in 2011. According to the lease terms, the developer had to complete the project within seven years.

news.title: Haryana RERA rejects Shree Vardhman Infra Heights' registry plea, freezes accounts
news.para: The authority in its order has said it granted as many as 24 opportunities to the developer to comply with the deficient requirements which were mandatory in order to renew or grant extension to the registration of the housing project.

news.title: Runwal Group forays into commercial realty with over Rs 4,500-crore investment over four years
news.para: The company will be developing a total of three commercial real estate projects in phases across Mumbai’s Kanjurmarg and Dombivli, and Viman Nagar in Pune. Of these, it has already started work on nearly 1 million sq ft in its Kanjurmarg project Runwal Commerz and Runwal Edge in Dombivli.

news.title: ED takes possession of Rs 245 crore worth Gurugram plots in PMLA case against Unitech
news.para: The money laundering case against the Unitech group, its promoter brothers -- Sanjay Chandra and Ajay Chandra -- and their family and others stems from multiple FIRs registered by the economic offences wing (EOW) of the Delhi Police.

news.title: China's Shimao Group seeks buyer for Hong Kong hotel: JLL
news.para: Shanghai-based Shimao, in the process of restructuring $11.8 billion of offshore debt, is among the many Chinese developers that defaulted last year.

news.title: DHFL case: SC dismisses ED appeal, says grant of default bail duration to include remand period
news.para: "The remand period will be calculated from the date, magistrate remand the accused. An accused becomes entitled to default bail if the charge sheet is not filed by 61st or 91st day of the remand period", the bench said.
